-- Patni Computer Gains in Mumbai Trading After Report IGate May Buy Stake
-- B y   S u r e s h   S e s h a d r i
-- 2010-12-27T03:48:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-27/patni-computer-shares-advance-in-mumbai-after-report-igate-may-buy-stake.html
Patni Computer Systems Ltd. climbed
in Mumbai trading after the Economic Times reported IGate Corp.,
backed by Apax Partners LLP, may buy 60 percent of the Indian
computer-services provider, without saying how it got the
information.  The stock rose 1.1 percent to 495.45 rupees as of 9:17 a.m.
local time.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Suresh Seshadri at 
 sseshadri1@bloomberg.net  